Pure integer model with external_body stubs; concurrency, pointers, and
fragment chains are deferred to C. Ref-count, alloc/free, push/pull,
add/remove paths are all bounds-checked and gate on ref_count/allocated > 0,
so the CVE-2023-5564 double-free class cannot be reached from within this
file's scope. No safety-relevant vulnerability in src/net_buf.rs proper;
any double-free would have to be in the companion C code.
